fields.description:
Impersonated user requests to Confluence are getting 401's from the REST API when using [OAuth 2.0 - JWT Bearer token|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/connect/docs/latest/concepts/OAuth2-JWT-Bearer-Token-Authentication.html] (add-on has ACT_AS_USER scope). The message in the response is below.
{code:java}
{ message: 'Client must be authenticated to access this resource.',
  'status-code': 401 }{code}
 

This is causing any connect add-on with Oauth based user impersonation to fail if they call @AsapAuth annotated rest resources

h3. Summary

REST API Get content couldn't find more than 100 items.
h3. Environment
{code:java}
919f9493398f8a14e7f8908cb6e2bc71d93f51d1 - Canary
Confluence 1000.1223.0{code}
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create more than 100 blogpost in a space
 # Run a REST API Get content call

{code:java}
https://example.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content?start=100&limit=25&spaceKey=SD&expand=history,body.view&type=blogpost{code}
h3. Expected Results
 * It should return more than 100 items

h3. Actual Results
 * Getting empty result

{code:java}
start=100&limit=25&spaceKey=SD&expand=history,body.view&type=blogpost
{"results":[],"start":100,"limit":25,"size":0,"_links":{"base":"https://theeagle-reborn.atlassian.net/wiki","context":"/wiki","prev":"/rest/api/content?spaceKey=SD&expand=history,body.view&limit=25&start=75&type=blogpost","self":"https://theeagle-reborn.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content?spaceKey=SD&expand=history,body.view&type=blogpost"}}{code}
